27/07/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu left on Wednesday (26 July) for a three-day official visit to the United States. 
His meeting Thursday with counterpart George W. 
Bush focuses on issues related to the agreement reached on US bases in Romania, the global fight against terrorism, and Bucharest's request to ease the US visa regime for Romanian citizens. 
In Washington, Basescu will also meet with World Bank officials. 
(Nine o'clock, Bucharest Daily News - 27/07/06; Rompres - 26/07/06)
